:R-HSA-180024  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Dopamine- and cAMP-regulated phosphoprotein, Mr 32 kDa (DARPP-32), was identified as a major target for dopamine and protein kinase A (PKA) in striatum. Recent advances now indicate that regulation DARPP-32 phosphorylation provides a mechanism for integrating information arriving at dopaminoceptive neurons, in multiple brain regions, via a variety of neurotransmitters, neuromodulators, neuropeptides, and steroid hormones. Activation of PKA or PKG stimulates DARPP-32 phosphorylation at Thr34, converting DARPP-32 into a potent inhibitor of protein phosphatase-1 (PP-1). DARPP-32 is also phosphorylated at Thr75 by Cdk5, converting DARPP-32 into an inhibitor of PKA. Thus, DARPP-32 has the unique property of being a dual-function protein, acting either as an inhibitor of PP-1 or of PKA." ;
        rdfs:label          "DARPP-32 events" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: Le Novere, N, Jassal, B, 2004-03-31 12:22:05" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Castagnoli, L, 2008-11-06 12:55:54" , "Edited: Jassal, Bijay, 2008-11-06" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-180024" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-111885/R-HSA-111885> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

